ledApp is a faceless background task for System 7.  It counts to 7 on an extended keyboard's lights until the shift and caps lock keysare pressed, or until it receives a quit Apple Event.ledApp demonstrates:¥ controlling the lights on a U.S. extended ADB keyboard¥ installing a repetitive time manager task, including  passing the A5 world and having the task wake up the  main program when necessary¥ making a notification manager call from a faceless background taskStart ledApp by double-clicking, or by placing it in the Startup Itemsfolder and restarting the Macintosh, or by changing its file type toappe and placing it in the Extensions folder and restarting.Grobbins      June 1991